# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: Other | Scene: CouncilMeeting2
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "It was a little over a week later when the first council meeting that included Marion and Varga began."
    new "It was a little over a week later when the first council meeting that included Marion and Varga began."

    old "Sarah and Thomas had arrived early, preparing ahead of the meeting, and it was Varga who showed up first, slightly too early."
    new "Sarah and Thomas had arrived early, preparing ahead of the meeting, and it was Varga who showed up first, slightly too early."

    old "My king, my princess."
    new "My king, my princess."

    old "Varga bowed as he entered, in that slightly fumbling way which only endeared him to Sarah."
    new "Varga bowed as he entered, in that slightly fumbling way which only endeared him to Sarah."

    old "It reminded her that there was a whole world outside of these walls, one where all the pomp and pretense of the court wasn't taken so seriously."
    new "It reminded her that there was a whole world outside of these walls, one where all the pomp and pretense of the court wasn't taken so seriously."

    old "Varga took his seat at the table, placing down a large stack of papers in front of himself."
    new "Varga took his seat at the table, placing down a large stack of papers in front of himself."

    old "I was hoping I wouldn't be late..."
    new "I was hoping I wouldn't be late..."

    old "Varga looks around the table."
    new "Varga looks around the table."

    old "But now I fear I might be too early."
    new "But now I fear I might be too early."

    old "Sarah laughed politely."
    new "Sarah laughed politely."

    old "Don't worry Lord Varga, I wish all the nobles could be as timely as yourself."
    new "Don't worry Lord Varga, I wish all the nobles could be as timely as yourself."

    old "Varga smiled at Sarah. His shoulders relaxed as the compliment put him visibly at ease."
    new "Varga smiled at Sarah. His shoulders relaxed as the compliment put him visibly at ease."

    old "Your invitation, Princess, it was great honour. I only hope that I can live up to the trust you place in me."
    new "Your invitation, Princess, it was great honour. I only hope that I can live up to the trust you place in me."

    old "My brother and I have no doubt that you will prove worthy of my trust."
    new "My brother and I have no doubt that you will prove worthy of my trust."

    old "The three continued to exchange pleasantries until the door swung upon."
    new "The three continued to exchange pleasantries until the door swung upon."

    old "Marion entered, strutting across the room and performing a perfect bow before sitting down."
    new "Marion entered, strutting across the room and performing a perfect bow before sitting down."

    old "King Thomas, princess Sarah, thank you for the invitation."
    new "King Thomas, princess Sarah, thank you for the invitation."

    old "Marion's eyes went around the table, settling finally on Varga."
    new "Marion's eyes went around the table, settling finally on Varga."

    old "Glad to see you managed to find your way here as well, Varga."
    new "Glad to see you managed to find your way here as well, Varga."

    old "The castle can be a confusing maze for those unfamiliar with it."
    new "The castle can be a confusing maze for those unfamiliar with it."

    old "Sarah watched the two exchange glances."
    new "Sarah watched the two exchange glances."

    old "She realized that whilst she had spoken to each of them, she had never seen the two men interact with one another."
    new "She realized that whilst she had spoken to each of them, she had never seen the two men interact with one another."

    old "There seemed to be a tension."
    new "There seemed to be a tension."

    old "Marion was flashing that wide grin of his, but Varga only scowled back at him."
    new "Marion was flashing that wide grin of his, but Varga only scowled back at him."

    old "Good to see you as well, Marion."
    new "Good to see you as well, Marion."

    old "Whatever played between the two men, neither seemed to want to escalate here."
    new "Whatever played between the two men, neither seemed to want to escalate here."

    old "There wasn't much time for the two to clash, for not long after, the three advisors entered the room and took their place between the men."
    new "There wasn't much time for the two to clash, for not long after, the three advisors entered the room and took their place between the men."

    old "General Barion, Spymaster Kravel and the Account Master Carolyn each greeted all the other attendants at the meeting."
    new "General Barion, Spymaster Kravel and the Account Master Carolyn each greeted all the other attendants at the meeting."

    old "After exchanging brief greetings, Thomas began the meeting by clearing his throat."
    new "After exchanging brief greetings, Thomas began the meeting by clearing his throat."

    old "Welcome, each of you, to today's council meeting."
    new "Welcome, each of you, to today's council meeting."

    old "As you might have noticed, we are joined by two new members to our council."
    new "As you might have noticed, we are joined by two new members to our council."

    old "Thomas waived his hand to one side."
    new "Thomas waived his hand to one side."

    old "We have Lord Varga, hero of Northwood, the man who broke the farmer uprising. He will be advising us on matters concerning war."
    new "We have Lord Varga, hero of Northwood, the man who broke the farmer uprising. He will be advising us on matters concerning war."

    old "Thomas waived his hand to the other side."
    new "Thomas waived his hand to the other side."

    old "And we have Lord Marion Achillea, of house Achillea. The loyalty of his family to our country stretches back to its very founding."
    new "And we have Lord Marion Achillea, of house Achillea. The loyalty of his family to our country stretches back to its very founding."

    old "He will be assisting us concerning the issues that have been brought up by the nobility."
    new "He will be assisting us concerning the issues that have been brought up by the nobility."

    old "General Barion was the first to speak."
    new "General Barion was the first to speak."

    old "King Thomas, excuse me, but as High General, I believe that should you have any questions on matters of war, you should consult me."
    new "King Thomas, excuse me, but as High General, I believe that should you have any questions on matters of war, you should consult me."

    old "Thomas seemed uncomfortable at being so directly confronted. Sarah decided to intercede on her brother's behalf."
    new "Thomas seemed uncomfortable at being so directly confronted. Sarah decided to intercede on her brother's behalf."

    old "General Barion, we understand your important contribution to our council, and we urge you to continue work on behalf of the royal army."
    new "General Barion, we understand your important contribution to our council, and we urge you to continue work on behalf of the royal army."

    old "However, King Thomas believes that given the current threats from the East, that he needs someone who is able to also tutor him on matters of war."
    new "However, King Thomas believes that given the current threats from the East, that he needs someone who is able to also tutor him on matters of war."

    old "We both understand that we are already asking a great deal of you, and so we did not wish to add onto your already great burden."
    new "We both understand that we are already asking a great deal of you, and so we did not wish to add onto your already great burden."

    old "General Barion stroked his great beard for a moment, but seemed pleased with the answer."
    new "General Barion stroked his great beard for a moment, but seemed pleased with the answer."

    old "Yes, it is true, I have been quite busy. An assistant to carry some of the load would be very welcome."
    new "Yes, it is true, I have been quite busy. An assistant to carry some of the load would be very welcome."

    old "Sarah looked at Varga, but if being called an assistant had offended him, he didn't show it."
    new "Sarah looked at Varga, but if being called an assistant had offended him, he didn't show it."

    old "Very well then, it's settled."
    new "Very well then, it's settled."

    old "The first issue on the agenda..."
    new "The first issue on the agenda..."

    old "Thomas shuffled through his papers for a while, trying to find what he was looking for."
    new "Thomas shuffled through his papers for a while, trying to find what he was looking for."

    old "This time it was Kravel who spoke up."
    new "This time it was Kravel who spoke up."

    old "It was concerning the tribes of the eastern desert."
    new "It was concerning the tribes of the eastern desert."

    old "Aah, yes...have we discovered anything new regarding that matter?"
    new "Aah, yes...have we discovered anything new regarding that matter?"

    old "Kravel nodded."
    new "Kravel nodded."

    old "Following the last council meeting, I organized a few scout parties to go into the eastern desert."
    new "Following the last council meeting, I organized a few scout parties to go into the eastern desert."

    old "I also reached out to my network of spies in the area, thin as it may be."
    new "I also reached out to my network of spies in the area, thin as it may be."

    old "We received nothing definitive, but they say there are hints of a large troop movement."
    new "We received nothing definitive, but they say there are hints of a large troop movement."

    old "Sarah leaned in."
    new "Sarah leaned in."

    old "Hints? What does that mean, exactly?"
    new "Hints? What does that mean, exactly?"

    old "They make mention of tracks, left on the outer steps, that could only be made by tens of thousands of horses."
    new "They make mention of tracks, left on the outer steps, that could only be made by tens of thousands of horses."

    old "There is a report that entire plots of grassland have turned arid."
    new "There is a report that entire plots of grassland have turned arid."

    old "As I said, nothing definitive, but it does appear there is an army on the move."
    new "As I said, nothing definitive, but it does appear there is an army on the move."

    old "Sarah turned to Thomas."
    new "Sarah turned to Thomas."

    old "We need to consider this seriously, Thomas. I think it's fair to say that it's more likely than not that an attack might come from the east."
    new "We need to consider this seriously, Thomas. I think it's fair to say that it's more likely than not that an attack might come from the east."

    old "Thomas nodded as he kept transfixed on the table."
    new "Thomas nodded as he kept transfixed on the table."

    old "Kravel shook his head."
    new "Kravel shook his head."

    old "No new reports or information. It's mostly been quiet on the frontier."
    new "No new reports or information. It's mostly been quiet on the frontier."

    old "Thomas looked at Sarah."
    new "Thomas looked at Sarah."

    old "See, sis, nothing to worry about. If there was an army out there, we'd have heard about it."
    new "See, sis, nothing to worry about. If there was an army out there, we'd have heard about it."

    old "Sarah nodded, but she was not entirely convinced."
    new "Sarah nodded, but she was not entirely convinced."

    old "It was Varga who now reared himself."
    new "It was Varga who now reared himself."

    old "Given what I've just heard, I believe that we ought to excercise caution."
    new "Given what I've just heard, I believe that we ought to excercise caution."

    old "We can't know for certain if there is an enemy waiting to strike, but we would do better to ready the army and prepare for the worst rather than hope for the best."
    new "We can't know for certain if there is an enemy waiting to strike, but we would do better to ready the army and prepare for the worst rather than hope for the best."

    old "Marion rolled his eyes."
    new "Marion rolled his eyes."

    old "That's a nice phrase, but it doesn't change reality."
    new "That's a nice phrase, but it doesn't change reality."

    old "Rosanna does not have infinite resources to commit to every phantom that the peasantry imagine in the dark."
    new "Rosanna does not have infinite resources to commit to every phantom that the peasantry imagine in the dark."

    old "If we waste resources here, that means sacrificing them somewhere else."
    new "If we waste resources here, that means sacrificing them somewhere else."

    old "I was out there, in the eastern district, with King Orwell. I saw no tribesmen, only farmers driving one another wild with conspiracy."
    new "I was out there, in the eastern district, with King Orwell. I saw no tribesmen, only farmers driving one another wild with conspiracy."

    old "A good ruler lets the facts guide him, not hysteria."
    new "A good ruler lets the facts guide him, not hysteria."

    old "Both Varga and Marion turn to Thomas, expecting him to settle the matter."
    new "Both Varga and Marion turn to Thomas, expecting him to settle the matter."

    old "Thomas turns to Sarah."
    new "Thomas turns to Sarah."

    old "We ready the army; best we be prepared."
    new "We ready the army; best we be prepared."

    old "Sarah turned her attention towards both, but making it clear she spoke on her brother's behalf."
    new "Sarah turned her attention towards both, but making it clear she spoke on her brother's behalf."

    old "Varga is right, if we prepare for nothing, then we lose nothing. But if the threat is real, we will be ready."
    new "Varga is right, if we prepare for nothing, then we lose nothing. But if the threat is real, we will be ready."

    old "Lord Barion, make preparations to rally Rosanna's army."
    new "Lord Barion, make preparations to rally Rosanna's army."

    old "Barion saluted the command."
    new "Barion saluted the command."

    old "Yes, Princess!"
    new "Yes, Princess!"

    old "We cannot afford to waste resources on fictions."
    new "We cannot afford to waste resources on fictions."

    old "Marion is right."
    new "Marion is right."

    old "Rallying the army means calling the soldiers from their homes and farms."
    new "Rallying the army means calling the soldiers from their homes and farms."

    old "If the threat proves fake, the people will resent us."
    new "If the threat proves fake, the people will resent us."

    old "Only if the threat proves real, should we rally the army."
    new "Only if the threat proves real, should we rally the army."

    old "Lady Carolyn spoke up."
    new "Lady Carolyn spoke up."

    old "Is this how the king decides?"
    new "Is this how the king decides?"

    old "Thomas asserted himself again."
    new "Thomas asserted himself again."

    old "Yes, we will act just as my sister said. It is the best option, given our circumstances."
    new "Yes, we will act just as my sister said. It is the best option, given our circumstances."

    old "With Thomas having spoken up, the matter was considered settled by all."
    new "With Thomas having spoken up, the matter was considered settled by all."

    old "After settling several smaller items, General Barion was the first to bring up another matter."
    new "After settling several smaller items, General Barion was the first to bring up another matter."

    old "My king, I must inform you that recent reports have found the city's walls to be dangerously weakened in some critical areas."
    new "My king, I must inform you that recent reports have found the city's walls to be dangerously weakened in some critical areas."

    old "Thomas suddenly sat up."
    new "Thomas suddenly sat up."

    old "Weakened? How? Our city hasn't been attacked in...I don't even know how long."
    new "Weakened? How? Our city hasn't been attacked in...I don't even know how long."

    old "General Barion nodded."
    new "General Barion nodded."

    old "This is correct, but in recent years the tide has been higher than ususal. This has favored our city's port, but it has had unexpected consequences."
    new "This is correct, but in recent years the tide has been higher than ususal. This has favored our city's port, but it has had unexpected consequences."

    old "The engineering corp informs me that the higher water levels have eroded the foundation of the city's walls along our coastal flanks."
    new "The engineering corp informs me that the higher water levels have eroded the foundation of the city's walls along our coastal flanks."

    old "Without urgent repairs, these defects could prove fatal should an enemy know how to exploit them."
    new "Without urgent repairs, these defects could prove fatal should an enemy know how to exploit them."

    old "Marion threw up his arms."
    new "Marion threw up his arms."

    old "Surely, we cannot be expected to fund every single pet project that the army comes up with?"
    new "Surely, we cannot be expected to fund every single pet project that the army comes up with?"

    old "As hard as it is to believe, the noble families while rich, are not infinitely so. Raising taxes so the engineering corp can play in the dirt, it's absurd."
    new "As hard as it is to believe, the noble families while rich, are not infinitely so. Raising taxes so the engineering corp can play in the dirt, it's absurd."

    old "Barion scowled at Marion."
    new "Barion scowled at Marion."

    old "As the council members were distracted by the bickering, Thomas leaned in close to Sarah and whispered."
    new "As the council members were distracted by the bickering, Thomas leaned in close to Sarah and whispered."

    old "What should we do?"
    new "What should we do?"

    old "Reinforce the walls; we can't let them collapse."
    new "Reinforce the walls; we can't let them collapse."

    old "Thomas nodded at Sarah and turned back to the council."
    new "Thomas nodded at Sarah and turned back to the council."

    old "I have made my decision."
    new "I have made my decision."

    old "We will reinforce the walls, the risks outweigh the costs."
    new "We will reinforce the walls, the risks outweigh the costs."

    old "Marion shook his head but said nothing."
    new "Marion shook his head but said nothing."

    old "The walls have stood just fine for centuries; they'll stand for centuries more."
    new "The walls have stood just fine for centuries; they'll stand for centuries more."

    old "The walls can wait, we must be wise on where we spend our money."
    new "The walls can wait, we must be wise on where we spend our money."

    old "With the matter settled, the council continued on, working through various other minute matters."
    new "With the matter settled, the council continued on, working through various other minute matters."

    old "Sarah idly listened as three different petitions for district land reforms were brought up and discussed."
    new "Sarah idly listened as three different petitions for district land reforms were brought up and discussed."

    old "Ruling, she had come to learn, happened as much in the grand moments as it did in the small."
    new "Ruling, she had come to learn, happened as much in the grand moments as it did in the small."

    old "Several hours later, with the last of the issues discussed, settled or pushed back, the advisors took their leave."
    new "Several hours later, with the last of the issues discussed, settled or pushed back, the advisors took their leave."

    old "As Sarah went to leave, she found Varga waiting for her."
    new "As Sarah went to leave, she found Varga waiting for her."

    old "Princess, uhm, Sarah, could I escort you?"
    new "Princess, uhm, Sarah, could I escort you?"

    old "Sarah smiled at Varga. She wondered if this man would ever get used to the trappings of nobility."
    new "Sarah smiled at Varga. She wondered if this man would ever get used to the trappings of nobility."

    old "Perhaps, she thought, past a certain age you could simply never internalize all the endless protocols and nuances of the royal court."
    new "Perhaps, she thought, past a certain age you could simply never internalize all the endless protocols and nuances of the royal court."

    old "Of course, Lord Varga."
    new "Of course, Lord Varga."

    old "She linked her arm through his."
    new "She linked her arm through his."

    old "But where are you escorting me to?"
    new "But where are you escorting me to?"

    old "Varga seemed flustered."
    new "Varga seemed flustered."

    old "I...I don't know, I thought...wherever you needed to go."
    new "I...I don't know, I thought...wherever you needed to go."

    old "Sarah softly laughed."
    new "Sarah softly laughed."

    old "The library is fine, I like to write down my thoughts on these meetings while they're still fresh."
    new "The library is fine, I like to write down my thoughts on these meetings while they're still fresh."

    old "Of course!"
    new "Of course!"

    old "Together, Sarah and Varga walked through the hallways of Castle Reinmeer, towards the library."
    new "Together, Sarah and Varga walked through the hallways of Castle Reinmeer, towards the library."

    old "{i}Who's escorting whom? Sarah thought to herself, as she corrected Varga a few times on the route to the library.{/i}"
    new "{i}Who's escorting whom? Sarah thought to herself, as she corrected Varga a few times on the route to the library.{/i}"

    old "The reason I wanted to escort you, Sarah, is that I wanted to thank you. In person, I mean."
    new "The reason I wanted to escort you, Sarah, is that I wanted to thank you. In person, I mean."

    old "Why is that?"
    new "Why is that?"

    old "Well, I know that the council is a prestigious position. And I know that there have not often been people of my...station, allowed to attend."
    new "Well, I know that the council is a prestigious position. And I know that there have not often been people of my...station, allowed to attend."

    old "Sarah could feel him grow more tense, the muscles in his arms flexing."
    new "Sarah could feel him grow more tense, the muscles in his arms flexing."

    old "It was true what he said. Most everyone on the council hailed from nobility, Varga was the rare exception."
    new "It was true what he said. Most everyone on the council hailed from nobility, Varga was the rare exception."

    old "But to Sarah it had seemed only logical. A way to break through the same old way of ruling."
    new "But to Sarah it had seemed only logical. A way to break through the same old way of ruling."

    old "People like Varga made up most of the nation, it seemed absurd to Sarah that they should not have a voice at the table."
    new "People like Varga made up most of the nation, it seemed absurd to Sarah that they should not have a voice at the table."

    old "I believe in merit, Varga. Your title, your birth, people here pretend like that's all that matters, but I'd rather have a hundred of you than some of these nobles."
    new "I believe in merit, Varga. Your title, your birth, people here pretend like that's all that matters, but I'd rather have a hundred of you than some of these nobles."

    old "Sarah's words seemed to lift Varga's spirits."
    new "Sarah's words seemed to lift Varga's spirits."

    old "It means a lot to hear you say that, Sarah."
    new "It means a lot to hear you say that, Sarah."

    old "Varga paused for a moment."
    new "Varga paused for a moment."

    old "So, how did I do? On the council meeting?"
    new "So, how did I do? On the council meeting?"

    old "Sarah patted his arm to comfort him."
    new "Sarah patted his arm to comfort him."

    old "You were great. I was afraid that you might have been intimidated by the setting and would say nothing, but I was glad that you spoke your mind about the army."
    new "You were great. I was afraid that you might have been intimidated by the setting and would say nothing, but I was glad that you spoke your mind about the army."

    old "Your background gives you a unique perspective. Use it, never feel like your voice doesn't matter."
    new "Your background gives you a unique perspective. Use it, never feel like your voice doesn't matter."

    old "All the other stuff, the protocols and rules of the court, you'll catch on soon enough."
    new "All the other stuff, the protocols and rules of the court, you'll catch on soon enough."

    old "Varga laughed, a little too loudly, at that."
    new "Varga laughed, a little too loudly, at that."

    old "It's weird. I commanded an army, led them to crush the rebellion, and watched thousands of men die in battle."
    new "It's weird. I commanded an army, led them to crush the rebellion, and watched thousands of men die in battle."

    old "And yet I've never felt the kind of uncertainty and unease on the battlefield as I do here at the court."
    new "And yet I've never felt the kind of uncertainty and unease on the battlefield as I do here at the court."

    old "Sarah listened as Varga entrusted his worries to her."
    new "Sarah listened as Varga entrusted his worries to her."

    old "We all have talents, things we're just naturally good at, and environments where we feel most comfortable."
    new "We all have talents, things we're just naturally good at, and environments where we feel most comfortable."

    old "But if we only did the things that come easy to us, we'd never grow or learn to challenge ourselves."
    new "But if we only did the things that come easy to us, we'd never grow or learn to challenge ourselves."

    old "She stopped walking and looked directly at Varga."
    new "She stopped walking and looked directly at Varga."

    old "This castle, this court, it can be what you make of it, Varga. You can see yourself as seperate from it, always feeling alienated, or you can become a part of it. Add to it."
    new "This castle, this court, it can be what you make of it, Varga. You can see yourself as seperate from it, always feeling alienated, or you can become a part of it. Add to it."

    old "Varga was moved by Sarah's words. He nodded in affirmation."
    new "Varga was moved by Sarah's words. He nodded in affirmation."

    old "You're right. I didn't mean to complain."
    new "You're right. I didn't mean to complain."

    old "You've given me a rare opportunity and I promise I will serve you and your brother as best I can."
    new "You've given me a rare opportunity and I promise I will serve you and your brother as best I can."

    old "I have no doubt that you will."
    new "I have no doubt that you will."

    old "Sarah felt Varga begin to move again, almost pulling her along."
    new "Sarah felt Varga begin to move again, almost pulling her along."

    old "Varga stopped, flustered, as he realized Sarah wasn't walking with him."
    new "Varga stopped, flustered, as he realized Sarah wasn't walking with him."

    old "Lord Varga..."
    new "Lord Varga..."

    old "Sorry, Princess, I...what did I do?"
    new "Sorry, Princess, I...what did I do?"

    old "Sarah gestured at the large door behind her."
    new "Sarah gestured at the large door behind her."

    old "We're at the library."
    new "We're at the library."

    old "I'm such an idiot...this place is like a maze, I honestly don't know how anyone finds anything."
    new "I'm such an idiot...this place is like a maze, I honestly don't know how anyone finds anything."

    old "Varga caught himself."
    new "Varga caught himself."

    old "Don't tell Marion I said that, please."
    new "Don't tell Marion I said that, please."

    old "I'll keep your secret."
    new "I'll keep your secret."

    old "Thank you for escorting me. I'll find my way in myself."
    new "Thank you for escorting me. I'll find my way in myself."

    old "Varga made a quick bow. He walked away, before turning around when Sarah called after him."
    new "Varga made a quick bow. He walked away, before turning around when Sarah called after him."

    old "Ooh, and Lord Varga...try not to get lost. It would be a shame for you to survive all those battles, only to lose your life wandering the halls of Castle Reinmeer."
    new "Ooh, and Lord Varga...try not to get lost. It would be a shame for you to survive all those battles, only to lose your life wandering the halls of Castle Reinmeer."

    old "She saw him turn red as he spun around and walked away, picking up his pace."
    new "She saw him turn red as he spun around and walked away, picking up his pace."

    old "Sarah sat down in the library and tried to focus her mind on her notes."
    new "Sarah sat down in the library and tried to focus her mind on her notes."

